# ğŸ› ï¸ WP-Deploy: WordPress Deployment & Database Management Scripts

WP-Deploy is a lightweight and efficient deployment tool for WordPress sites using Docker. It provides automated database backups, restores, and deployment workflows for syncing local and remote environments.

## ğŸ“Œ Features
âœ” **Automated Deployments** â†’ Deploy WordPress updates to a remote server.
âœ” **Database Backup & Restore** â†’ Securely backup and restore the database.
âœ” **Global CLI Access** â†’ Install scripts system-wide for easy execution.
âœ” **Configurable Settings** â†’ Uses `wp-deploy.ini` for environment-specific settings.
âœ” **Safe File Synchronization** â†’ Uses `rsync` for efficient file transfers.
âœ” **Modular Structure** â†’ Scripts can be used independently or together.

---

## ğŸ“‚ Directory Structure

```
ğŸ“¦ wp-deploy/
 â”£ ğŸ“œ wp-db-backup         # Script to create a database backup
 â”£ ğŸ“œ wp-db-restore        # Script to restore a database backup
 â”£ ğŸ“œ wp-deploy            # Script to deploy changes to a remote server
 â”£ ğŸ“œ wp-pull-from-remote  # Script to sync the latest production data locally
 â”£ ğŸ“œ wp-functions         # Shared functions for deployment and database management
 â”£ ğŸ“œ install              # Script to install wp-deploy commands globally
 â”£ ğŸ“œ wp-deploy.ini.sample    # Sample configuration file (copy to wp-deploy.ini)
 â”£ ğŸ“œ README.md            # Documentation
```

